-- E.ON Russia net profit down 15 pct in H1 2014
-- By Anastasia Lyrchikova
-- Thu Aug 21, 2014 02:25AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, Aug 21 (Reuters) - E.ON Russia <EONR.MM>, the Russian subsidiary of Germany's E.On <EONGn.DE>, said on Thursday its first-half net income fell 15 percent, year-on-year.

Net income fell to 8.0 billion roubles ($220 million) from 9.4 billion roubles in the first half of 2013 and revenues grew 2 percent to 39.3 billion roubles, the company said in a report.